  {"slug":"implied-volatility","title":"Implied Volatility (Bisection)","description":"## Implied Volatility\n\nGiven a market call price, find implied volatility using **bisection method**.\n\nSearch in range [0.001, 5.0] with tolerance 1e-6. Max 200 iterations.","difficulty":"hard","category":"options","starter_code":"def implied_vol(market_price: float, S: float, K: float, T: float, r: float) -> float:\n    pass\n","solution_code":"import math\ndef implied_vol(market_price,S,K,T,r):\n    def N(x): return (1+math.erf(x/math.sqrt(2)))/2\n    def bs(s):\n        d1=(math.log(S/K)+(r+s**2/2)*T)/(s*T**0.5)\n        d2=d1-s*T**0.5\n        return S*N(d1)-K*math.exp(-r*T)*N(d2)\n    lo,hi=0.001,5.0\n    for _ in range(200):\n        mid=(lo+hi)/2\n        if bs(mid)>market_price: hi=mid\n        else: lo=mid\n        if hi-lo<1e-6: break\n    return (lo+hi)/2\n","test_cases":{"cases":[{"input":{"market_price":10.4506,"S":100.0,"K":100.0,"T":1.0,"r":0.05},"expected":0.2}],"function":"implied_vol"},"tags":["implied-vol","bisection","options"],"points":200},

