  {"slug":"expected-shortfall","title":"Expected Shortfall (CVaR)","description":"## Expected Shortfall\n\nES = mean of losses beyond VaR threshold.\n\n`ES = -mean(returns where returns < -VaR)`","difficulty":"medium","category":"risk","starter_code":"def expected_shortfall(returns: list, confidence: float = 0.95) -> float:\n    pass\n","solution_code":"def expected_shortfall(returns,confidence=0.95):\n    s=sorted(returns); n=len(s)\n    cutoff=int((1-confidence)*n)\n    tail=s[:max(1,cutoff)]\n    return -sum(tail)/len(tail)\n","test_cases":{"cases":[{"input":{"returns":[-0.05,-0.03,-0.01,0.01,0.02,0.04,0.06,-0.02,0.03,-0.04],"confidence":0.9},"expected":0.05}],"function":"expected_shortfall"},"tags":["cvar","es","risk"],"points":125},

  {"slug":"sortino-ratio","title":"Sortino Ratio","description":"## Sortino Ratio\n\nSortino = `(annualized_return - target) / downside_deviation`\n\nDownside deviation uses only negative returns vs target (default 0). Use ddof=1. Annualize by sqrt(252).","difficulty":"medium","category":"risk","starter_code":"def sortino_ratio(returns: list, target: float = 0.0) -> float:\n    pass\n","solution_code":"import math\ndef sortino_ratio(returns,target=0.0):\n    ann=sum(returns)/len(returns)*252\n    neg=[r-target for r in returns if r<target]\n    if not neg: return 0.0\n    dd=(sum(x**2 for x in neg)/(len(neg)-1))**0.5*252**0.5 if len(neg)>1 else 0.0\n    return 0.0 if dd==0 else (ann-target*252)/dd\n","test_cases":{"cases":[{"input":{"returns":[0.0]*10,"target":0.0},"expected":0.0}],"function":"sortino_ratio"},"tags":["sortino","risk","performance"],"points":125},

